sql:
SELECT COUNT(student_id) AS number_of_students
FROM student_major
WHERE major_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "sophomore students" refers to students in their second year of study;
- "successfully navigated the core curriculum" means the students have completed the required core courses;
- "guided by the wisdom of the Computer Science department's sages" means the courses were taught by instructors from the Computer Science department.

- 'blossoms of knowledge' refers to courses;
- 'watered by the stream' refers to being enrolled in;
- 'field of Computer Science' refers to the major.

- "Core courses" are fundamental courses required for a specific major;
- "Semester 1" refers to the first half of the academic year;
- "2023" is the academic year in which the courses are being offered.

sql:
SELECT course_id, required_credits
FROM core_courses
WHERE major_id = (SELECT major_id FROM majors WHERE major_name = 'INFO');

SELECT major_id, concentration
FROM student_major
WHERE major_id = 0 AND concentration = 'Software Development';

SELECT COUNT(student_id) AS number_of_students
FROM enrollments
WHERE course_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT T1.student_id
FROM enrollments AS T1
JOIN enrollments AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id AND T1.semester = T2.semester AND T1.course_id != T2.course_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'A' grade is typically the highest grade in a grading system, indicating excellent performance;
- Credits are units used to measure the amount of course work completed by a student;
- The query focuses on students' first names, suggesting a simplified or informal approach to identifying students.

- "sapling" refers to students;
- "garden" refers to the major;
- "more than one sapling" means the major has more than one student enrolled.

- "Core courses" refer to the courses that are mandatory for a specific major;
- "SWEN" stands for Software Engineering major;
- "Completed all core courses" means the total credits earned by the student for core courses are equal to the required credits for the major;
- "Not taken any core courses" means the student has not earned any credits for core courses.
